Kaduna State deputy Governor Barnabas Bala Bantex has lost his bid to represent his people in the senate. Bantex who contested on the platform of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) lost his election to the incumbent Senator representing Southern Kaduna Senatorial zone, Danjuma Laah. Laah who contested on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party, (PDP) has been declared winner of the Southern Kaduna Senatorial District. The Returning Officer, Dr. Suleiman Hashim said Senator Laah won with a total vote of 268, 923 while Kadunaâ€™s deputy governor and candidate of the APC, Barnabas Bala Bantex polled 133, 287 votes.